article.headline: Tenn.-Martin 75, Tennessee St. 74
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Lester Hudson, the nation's second leading scorer, scored 27 points including two free throws with 1 second left to lead Tennessee-Martin to a 75-74 win Monday over Tennessee State. Hudson, scoring his season average, made 9-of-18 field goals and all three of his free throws. Two free throws by Tenn-Martin's Carlos Wright had made it 74-73 with seven seconds left. Marquis Weddle had 12 points, and Sam Pearson and Djero Riedewald added 10 points each for Tennessee-Martin (7-9, 3-3 Ohio Valley Conference). Tennessee State (5-9, 2-3 OVC) was led by Darius Cox with 23 points, Jerrell Houston with 18 and Bruce Price with 16. Cox was 7-of-9 from the floor and 9-of-10 from the free throw line. Tennessee-Martin led 37-34 at the half. Price missed a 3-pointer at the buzzer that would have won it for the Tigers.
